description: Here is a great example of a beautiful true 1967 Camaro Rally Sport (not a clone) convertible in excellent condition. The car has a 327 V8 engine that runs strong mated to a Turbo 350 transmission.  The car has front disk brakes and rear drum brakes as well as A/C. The body is in excellent condition with pristine paint (as you can see in the pictures). I acquired the car in 2004 from down in Florida and had it inspected with a fine tooth comb, repairing anything that was found to be less than perfect mechanically and cosmetically.  It has lived in a humidity controlled garage ever since.  I have extensive records of the work that was done.  I also have many of the original parts that will be included with the car along with new chrome pieces that I never installed.

The stereo is a Custom Auto Sound Am/FM/cassette/cd changer with a control head that replicates the look of the original AM radio. A pair of Eclipse 5.25” speakers were installed in the kick panels, Pioneer Ts-X150 enclosed speakers sit on the floor behind the front seats and have connectors some they can easily be removed.  A pair of Eclipse SW6103.4 10” sub-woofers reside in a Soundcraft enclosure in the trunk.

A presale inspection completed by MotorTech Appraisals only lists two minor issues: the carpet is a little faded and the frame for the convertible roof has some minor surface rust.  I have new, in the box, replacement carpet that will go with the car and the roof frame can be easily prepped and painted.

If you're looking for a time capsule Camaro, this is it! This is an immaculately restored 1968 Camaro, true RS car. True to build sheet, this highly optioned car features power brakes, steering, tilt column, floor shift, tic-toc-tac, houndstooth interior, black vinyl roof, and red line tires just to name a few!

Under the hood, you'll find a cleanly detailed 327CI V8 with lots of chrome, however the original valve covers and breather are also included to return to the stock look if you choose. The engine runs great and sounds amazing though the dual flowmaster exhaust.
This is easily one of the cleanest first-gen camaros youll ever see. Don't let this one slip away!

Stunning! This car looks hot, especially in the sunlight. The color and the quality of the finish makes this car stand out. The stinger hood and chrome wheels don't hurt either. The deluxe interior is cool too. It has contoured sports seats and suede integrated in the upholstery. Powered by a 1967 Chevelle 396-350 hp engine. Upgrades push it closer to 400 hp. Has Offenhauser intake, big Holley carb, HEI ignition and some internal improvements. Coated headers and Flowmaster exhaust make it rumble. Kept cool with aluminum water pump and radiator. Has Ride Tech tubular control arms, rack and pinion steering, welded frame connectors, rear adjustable tubular control arms and adjustable gas shocks. Has Wilwood 4 wheel disc brakes. Upgraded halo LED lights, quick electric doors. New chrome Torque Thrust ll wheels and BFG tires. It's a great driver. Paint is slick, chrome, trim, rubber and glass are great. Interior is restored from carpet to headliner. Upgraded leather wheel. Its a radio and heater delete. Currently one of my favorites!

This 1968 Camaro RS/SS is ready to tear up the open road! With only 5000 miles on a rebuilt 355 cubic inch small block V8 there are plenty of miles and good times left on this iconic classic muscle car. The engine was rebuilt using high end parts including; TRW forged flat top pistons hardened valve seats to run unleaded ARP rod bolts Crane Blazer cam Crane Pro-Series pushrods Lunati Voodoo roller rockers 1.5 Lunati hydraulic lifters and Melling pushrod guide plates. Sitting on top of it all is 650 Speed Demon carburetor feeding it The MSD Pro-Billet distributor MSD 6AL electronic ignition control MSD blaster 2 coil and MSD 8.5 heli-core wires provide a strong spark to max to ensure proper combustion. The exhaust gasses are released quickly through a set of ceramic coated long tube Hooker headers that give off a powerful growl! As you approach this Camaro and open up the door to get in you will notice quickly the completely reupholstered interior with hounds tooth inserts in the seat setting the sixties style off right. As you slide in and get behind the wheel fire it up the engine comes to life quickly. Put the top loader four-speed manual transmission in first release the clutch and start to cruise! The power is available at the blip of a throttle and the competition Engineering A-link traction bars subframe connectors and aftermarket bushing provide a firm yet comfortable ride. This car is mechanically solid and is ready for the next owner to take for drives on the weekend! This vehicle is located in our Denver showroom. The first generation of Camaro was built for the 1967 through 1969 model year. And even though that seems like a short run, these cars are still some of the most collectible Camaros depending on the Engine and Appearance package you chose, and there were many. Engine options were as many as 12 in 1969 with three main packages that included the RS, SS and Z/28 with several special packages sold through GM and specialized dealers of performance parts and installation.

This particular RS/SS Camaro is a very well done.  It is powered by a 383 stroker v8 with according to the owner capable of 500 horsepower.  The car was restored in 2005 and shows very well.  The Camaro has power brakes(discs in front and rear), power steering, headers, aluminum radiator, aluminum heads, Auto meter gauges, console shift, front bucket seats, Billet Specialties steering wheel, Kenwood CD player, Boyd Coddington wheels, Toyo tires, tinted windows, dual exhaust and more.  This is a stud inside, outside, and underneath! It's a lot of fun to drive and an absolute head turner. Please call or email for more details!
